The ghist of the thing is that the dark elf is trying to get rid of the bad image of dark elves by doing good deeds.  She’s seen visiting somebody’s house, but he turns her away due to her outfit. The boy, an orphan living alone, asks her to come to house and asks for various favors like food and chores, which he couldn’t do alone.  The boy then grows up, and has become self-sufficient, farming and declining her offer of instantly hunting meat, saying his own rice would suffice.  She then says she was going to depart to do good deeds elsewhere, and says whether he has one last wish, pressing him when he hesitates. He replies that he would like to have a child between him and the dark elf, to which she agrees after some surprise. It’s the first time for both of them, and they confess love to each other. 70 years later, she’s at his grave for a final farewell, leaving with their two children for her original quest of doing good deeds.
